title: NASA's Perseverance Captures Dust-Filled Martian Whirlwind
summary: The six-wheeled geologist spotted the twister as part of an atmospheric exploration of Jezero Crater.

title: Ispace revises design of lunar lander for NASA CLPS mission
summary: The American subsidiary of Japanese company ispace has revised the design of a lunar lander it is providing for a NASA mission, pushing back the launch of that mission by a year.

title: European Commission Launches Targeted Consultation for EU Space Law
summary:
The European Commission has launched a targeted stakeholder consultation for an EU Space Law that could be adopted in 2024. The creation of an EU Space Law (EUSL) was identified as a priority for the Commission during a 13 September State of the Union address from President Ursula von der Leyen. title: China to attempt lunar far side sample return in 2024
summary: China will launch its Chang’e-6 lunar sample return mission next year in an attempt at a first-ever collection of material from the far side of the moon.

title: NASA delays Psyche launch a week
summary: NASA has postponed the launch of the asteroid mission Psyche a week to update the configuration of thrusters on the spacecraft.

title: Rogers to continue to challenge decision to keep Space Command in Colorado
summary: he chairman of the House Armed Services Committee Rep. Mike Rogers (R-Ala.) during a hearing Sept. 28 grilled military officials over their role in the Biden administration’s decision to keep U.S. Space Command’s headquarters in Colorado.

title: Blue Origin, Sierra Space weigh future of Orbital Reef space station as partnership turns rocky
summary: The Orbital Reef space station partnership between Jeff Bezos’ Blue Origin and Sierra Space is on rocky footing, CNBC has learned.

title: Astroscale inspector satellite ready for launch
summary: Astroscale says a mission to inspect an upper stage abandoned in low Earth orbit, as a precursor to removing it, is ready for launch, but a recent launch failure will keep it on the ground for the time being.

title: SpaceX to close out third quarter with record-breaking Starlink mission
summary: SpaceX is set to close the third quarter of 2023 with its 70th launch of the year. The mission, Starlink Group 6-19, is set to lift off this Friday, Sept. 29, at 6:39 PM EDT (22:29 UTC) from Space Launch Complex 40 (SLC-40), at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida.
